Sections:\\n\\n- **`server/StateApplierCli.cs`** — Main file, completely rewritten\\n  - Removed: `LegacyOptions` record, `RunLegacy()`, `ApplyLegacy()`, `ApplyLegacyDryRun()`, `RunLegacyPostApply()`, `IsAlreadyAppliedWithLog()`, `ValidateRequest()`, `ValidateHumanDecision()`, `ValidateCandidate()`, `LegacyPostApplyError()`, `ParseLegacyArgs()`\\n  - Removed `Root` field from `PrepareOptions` and `ApplyOptions` records\\n  - Added `ValidTransitionKinds` HashSet: `{\\\"NORMAL\\\", \\\"PHASE_CHANGE\\\", \\\"RECOVERY\\\", \\\"REPLAY\\\"}`\\n  - Added `internal static Func<string?>? FailAfterWriteHook;`\\n  - `Run()` now returns exit 2 + usage for any subcommand other than `prepare`/`apply`\\n  - `RunApply()` has unknown kind check BEFORE `HighRiskKinds` check, removed `canonicalMode`\\n  - `RunApplyCommitPhase()`: removed `canonicalMode` param, projection always runs, uses `FailAfterWriteHook` not env var\\n  - `Rollback()`: removed `canonicalMode` param, projection always runs\\n  - `CheckExistingTransition()`: recomputes hash from fields → check `computed vs log.hash` first (collision), then `envelope.contractSha vs computed` (mismatch)\\n  - `ValidateStatusTransition()`: removed `humanDecisionPath` param; `completed` is terminal\\n  - Added `LoadWorkstateContext()` helper to reduce `RunApply` below 80-line limit\\n\\n  Key new logic in `CheckExistingTransition()`:\\n  ```csharp\\n  var computed = ComputeContractHash(\\n      envelope.TransitionId, envelope.TransitionKind, envelope.RequestSha256,\\n      envelope.ExpectedPreStateSha256, envelope.ExpectedPostStateSha256, envelope.EffectiveAt);\\n\\n  if (!string.Equals(computed, logInfo.TransitionContractSha256, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))\\n      return Fail(1, envelope.TransitionId, \\\"transition-id-collision\\\", ...);\\n\\n  if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(envelope.TransitionContractSha256) &&\\n      !string.Equals(envelope.TransitionContractSha256, computed, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))\\n      return Fail(1, envelope.TransitionId, \\\"envelope-contract-mismatch\\\", ...);\\n\\n  return ReportIdempotent(envelope.TransitionId);\\n  ```\\n\\n  `LoadWorkstateContext()` helper (added to fix 81-line violation):\\n  ```csharp\\n  private static (string root, string workstatePath, string logPath, byte[] rawBytes, JsonObject workstate, string rawStr)?\\n      LoadWorkstateContext()\\n  {\\n      try\\n      {\\n          var root = GitTools.FindRepoRoot();\\n          var wsPath = Path.Combine(root, \\\"docs\\\", \\\"handoff\\\", \\\"WORKSTATE.json\\\");\\n          var lPath = Path.Combine(root, \\\"docs\\\", \\\"handoff\\\", \\\"WORKSTATE.applier-log.jsonl\\\");\\n          if (!File.Exists(wsPath)) { WriteError(\\\"WORKSTATE.json not found\\\"); return null; }\\n          var bytes = File.ReadAllBytes(wsPath);\\n          var raw = Encoding.UTF8.GetString(bytes);\\n          var ws = JsonNode.Parse(raw)?.AsObject()\\n              ?? throw new InvalidOperationException(\\\"WORKSTATE.json is not a valid JSON object\\\");\\n          return (root, wsPath, lPath, bytes, ws, raw);\\n      }\\n      catch (Exception ex) { WriteError(ex.Message); return null; }\\n  }\\n  ```\\n\\n- **`server/Harness/StateTransitionCallsiteCheckCli.cs`** — Rewritten scope fix\\n  - `ActiveExtensions`: added `.md`\\n  - `HistoricalPrefixes`: removed `\\\"outputs/launch/\\\"`, added `\\\"docs/handoff/queue/\\\"` and `\\\"outputs/review/\\\"`\\n  - `EnumerateActiveFiles()`: added `Path.Combine(root, \\\".github\\\")` to `scanDirs`\\n  - Root scanning extended: added `\\\"*.json\\\"`, `\\\"*.yaml\\\"`, `\\\"*.yml\\\"` to root-level file scan\\n  - `IsHistorical()`: also handles exact file match (`.TrimEnd('/')`)\\n\\n  New `HistoricalPrefixes`:\\n  ```csharp\\n  private static readonly string[] HistoricalPrefixes =\\n  [\\n      \\\"docs/handoff/sessions/\\\",\\n      \\\"docs/handoff/WORKSTATE.applier-log.jsonl\\\",\\n      \\\"docs/handoff/RECOVERY.md\\\",\\n      \\\"docs/handoff/queue