textFromRoot(string root)` (removes the internal `GitTools.FindRepoRoot()` call)\\n  - Fixed `CheckExistingTransition`: added contract hash check for NEW transitions (before the old `if (!isInState) return null`)\\n  - Modified `RunApplyCommitPhase`: replaced `ProjectionCli.Run([\\\"projection\\\"])` with `RunProjection()`\\n  - Modified `Rollback`: added `if (FailRestoreForTest) throw new InvalidOperationException(...)` before file restore; replaced `ProjectionCli.Run([\\\"projection\\\"])` with `RunProjection()`\\n  - Added `ValidateOptions(Dictionary<string,string> map, HashSet<string> knownKeys)` helper\\n  - Added `RunProjection()` helper: `ProjectionOverride is not null ? ProjectionOverride() : ProjectionCli.Run([\\\"projection\\\"])`\\n  - Added `RunSelfTest()`, `RunSelfTestInDir(string tmpRoot)`, `RestoreFixture(wsPath, wsContent, logPath)` — full self-test implementation\\n\\n  Key new code for `CheckExistingTransition` fix:\\n  ```csharp\\n  if (!isInState)\\n  {\\n      if (!string.IsNullOrWhiteSpace(envelope.TransitionContractSha256))\\n      {\\n          var computed = ComputeContractHash(\\n              envelope.TransitionId, envelope.TransitionKind, envelope.RequestSha256,\\n              envelope.ExpectedPreStateSha256, envelope.ExpectedPostStateSha256, envelope.EffectiveAt);\\n          if (!string.Equals(envelope.TransitionContractSha256, computed, StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))\\n              return Fail(1, envelope.TransitionId, \\\"envelope-contract-mismatch\\\",\\n                  \\\"envelope.transitionContractSha256이 계산값과 다릅니다 — 위조 또는 수정됨\\\");\\n      }\\n      return null; // 정상 경로로 진행.\\n  }\\n  ```\\n\\n  **CURRENT COMPILE ERRORS (2)**:\\n  - Line 271: `'opts' 이름이 현재 컨텍스트에 없습니다.` — In `ApplyEnvelopeCore`, there is still a reference to `opts.DryRun` which should be `dryRun` (the parameter)\\n  - Line 559: `'computed'인 지역 또는 매개 변수는 이 범위에서 선언될 수 없음` — The newly added `var computed` in the `!isInState` block conflicts with an existing `var computed` later in the same method (`CheckExistingTransition`); one must be renamed (e.g., `newEnvelopeComputed`)\\n\\n- **`server/Harness/StateTransitionCallsiteCheckCli.cs`** (NOT YET MODIFIED — pending):\\n  - Need to add `.txt` to `ActiveExtensions` array (currently: `.cs .ps1 .sh .cmd .bat .json .yaml .yml .md`)\\n  - Need to replace prefix-based `HistoricalPrefixes` array + `IsHistorical()` method with explicit file list read from `docs/handoff/CALLSITE-HISTORICAL.json`\\n\\n- **`docs/handoff/CALLSITE-HISTORICAL.json`** (NOT YET CREATED — pending):\\n  Files with legacy patterns found via grep (that currently scan as historical):\\n  - `docs/handoff/queue/directive-06C-1-R1-legacy-removal.md`\\n  - `docs/verification/06c1-r1-legacy-removal.md`\\n  - `outputs/review/06C-1-R1.codex.md`\\n  - `outputs/review/06C-1.codex.md`\\n  - `outputs/reviewer-log.md`\\n  (No `.prompt.txt` files have legacy patterns; `.jsonl` files are not scanned with extension-based approach)\\n\\n- **`docs/verification/06c1-r2-strict-cli.md`** (NOT YET CREATED — pending report):\\n  Must include pre-fix outputs for criteria 2, 3, 9, 10, 11\\n\\n- **`server/Harness/HandoffIntegrityCli.cs`** (READ ONLY — pattern to follow):\\n  - `RunSelfTest()` pattern: creates array of test cases, calls `HandoffIntegrityChecker.Run()` with fixture paths, compares expected vs actual failure codes\\n  - Uses `docs/qa/fixtures/reconciliation/pending/` directory for fixtures\\n\\n4. Errors and Fixes:\\n\\n- **Compile error: `opts` not in scope (line 271 of StateApplierCli.cs)**:\\n  - Cause: After refactoring `RunApply` to extract `ApplyEnvelopeCore(ctx, envelope, dryRun)`, the new function body still has a leftover reference to `opts.DryRun` from the original code\\n  - Fix needed: Replace `opts.DryRun` with `dryRun` (the `bool dryRun` parameter of `ApplyEnvelopeCore`)\\n\\n- **Compile error: `computed` variable name conflict (line 559 of StateApplierCli.cs)**:\\n  - Cause: In `CheckExistingTransition